<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">

<Paragraph>
This sample illustrates grouping and ungrouping of shapes in XlsIO.
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>
Essential XlsIO allows to group multiple shapes and ungroup the shapes in worksheet. The <Bold> IGroupShape </Bold> interface is the in-memory representation of the
group shapes in an Excel workbook.
</Paragraph>

<BlockUIContainer>
<TextBlock Style="{DynamicResource HeaderTextStyle}">Features:</TextBlock>
</BlockUIContainer>
<Paragraph>This sample demonstrates following features:</Paragraph>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Grouping multiple shapes into a single group shape.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Ungroup the group shape and all its inner shapes.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>

